gao.dbmanager

Class DBParameters

  • java.lang.Object
    • gao.dbmanager.DBParameters

  • public class DBParameters
extends java.lang.Object
    Class represents the values which are needed to connect a database. For each database (usually) a special connection-string, driver etc. is necessary. Use the create"YOUR-DATABASE"DBParameters-Method to create a parameter-object for your database. It is also possible to create connection-string by yourself and than use createDBParameters. In this case you also have to know which jdbc-driver you want to use.
    Version:
    0.9
    Author:
    Martin Beyer

      • createDBParameters

        public static DBParameters createDBParameters(java.lang.String pConnectionString,
                              java.lang.String pUser,
                              java.lang.String pPassword,
                              java.lang.String pSchemaName,
                              java.lang.String pDriverName,
                              java.lang.Integer pErrorCode)
                                       throws DBManagerException
        Creates a database-independent parameter-object.
        Parameters:
        pConnectionString - connection-string for the database
        pUser - user-name to connect as
        pPassword - password for authentication
        pSchemaName - name of the schema that should be used
        pDriverName - name of the jdbc-driver
        pErrorCode - SQLException-code if a table already exists
        Returns:
        DBParameters
        Throws:
        DBManagerException

      • getConnection

        public java.sql.Connection getConnection()
                                  throws java.lang.ClassNotFoundException,
                                         java.sql.SQLException
        Creates a Connection to the database. If a DataSource is available it will be used, otherwise the DriverManager.
        Returns:
        A Connection or null if the connection attempt failed without throwing an exception.
        Throws:
        java.lang.ClassNotFoundException - If no fitting driver could be found.
